'''痛苦'''（{{lang-en|Suffering}}），可能是一種不[[愉快|愉快]]和[[厭惡|厭惡]]的[[體驗|體驗]]，與個人對[[傷害|傷害]]或傷害威脅的[[感知|感知]]有關。<ref>For instance, Wayne Hudson in Historicizing Suffering, Chapter 14 of Perspectives on Human Suffering (Jeff Malpas and Norelle Lickiss, editors, Springer, 2012) : "According to the standard account suffering is a universal human experience described as a negative basic feeling or emotion that involves a subjective character of unpleasantness, aversion, harm or threat of harm to body or mind (Spelman 1997; Cassell 1991)."</ref> 痛苦是構成[[情感_(心理學)|情感]]現象負面效價（英語：Valence）的基本要素。痛苦的反面是[[快樂|快樂]]或[[幸福|幸福]]等。

痛苦通常被歸類為[[身體|身體]]上的<ref>Examples of physical suffering: [[pain|pain]] of various types, excessive heat, excessive cold, [[itching|itching]], [[hunger|hunger]], [[thirst|thirst]], [[nausea|nausea]], [[air_hunger|air hunger]], [[sleep_deprivation|sleep deprivation]]. {{cite web|title=IASP Pain Terminology|url=http://www.iasp-pain.org/AM/Template.cfm?Section%3DGeneral_Resource_Links%26Template%3D%2FCM%2FHTMLDisplay.cfm%26ContentID%3D3058|access-date=September 11, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080926205544/http://www.iasp-pain.org/AM/Template.cfm?Section=General_Resource_Links&Template=%2FCM%2FHTMLDisplay.cfm&ContentID=3058|archive-date=September 26, 2008|url-status=dead}}{{cite web|title=UAB – School of Medicine – Center for Palliative and Supportive Care|url=http://www.palliative.uab.edu/response/|access-date=2008-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071028180547/http://www.palliative.uab.edu/response/|archive-date=2007-10-28|url-status=live}} Other examples are given by L. W. Sumner, on p. 103 of [https://books.google.com/books?id=tjua97jPvEYC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=suffering+sumner+happiness&source=bl&ots=ZyDU9Tqs6H&sig=kgb_8YA1EFDjufwDCACs6w99ND8&hl=en&ei=w9qbSs-3Ns-G8QaTufDCBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=&f=false Welfare, Happiness, and Ethics] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tjua97jPvEYC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=suffering+sumner+happiness&source=bl&ots=ZyDU9Tqs6H&sig=kgb_8YA1EFDjufwDCACs6w99ND8&hl=en&ei=w9qbSs-3Ns-G8QaTufDCBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=&f=false |date=20211221082506 }}: "Think for a moment of the many physical symptoms which, when persistent, can make our lives miserable: nausea, hiccups, sneezing, dizziness, disorientation, loss of balance, itching, 'pins and needles', 'restless legs', tics, twitching, fatigue, difficulty in breathing, and so on."</ref>或[[心智|心智]]上的。<ref>Mental suffering can also be called psychological or emotional (see [[Psychological_pain|Psychological pain]]). Examples of mental suffering: [[depression_(mood)|depression (mood)]] / [[hopelessness|hopelessness]], [[grief|grief]], [[sadness|sadness]] / [[loneliness|loneliness]] / [[Broken_heart|heartbreak]], [[disgust|disgust]], [[irritation|irritation]], [[anger|anger]], [[jealousy|jealousy]], [[envy|envy]], [[Taṇhā|craving or yearning]], [[frustration|frustration]], [[anguish|anguish]], [[angst|angst]], [[fear|fear]], [[anxiety|anxiety]] / [[panic|panic]], [[shame|shame]] / [[Guilt_(emotion)|guilt]], [[Regret_(emotion)|regret]], [[embarrassment|embarrassment]] / [[humiliation|humiliation]], [[Psychomotor_agitation|restlessness]].</ref> 它可能有各種程度的強度，從輕微到無法忍受。持續[[時間|時間]]長度和發生[[頻率|頻率]]的因素通常與強度因素相結合。受苦者或其他人對痛苦的[[態度_(心理學)|態度]]可能有很大差異，這取決於它被認為是可以避免或不可避免、有用或無用、值得或不值得的。

苦在各種生物的[[生命|生命]]中以多種方式發生，經常是[[戲劇|戲劇]]性的。因此，人類活動的許多領域都與痛苦的某些方面有關。這些方面可能包括痛苦的性質、過程、起源和原因和意義、相關的個人、社會和文化行為<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Suffering, hope, and entrapment: Resilience and cultural values in Afghanistan|last=Eggerman, Panter Brick|first=Mark, Catherine|date=2010|journal=Social Science & Medicine|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.socscimed.2010.03.023|volume=71|pages=71–83|pmc=3125115|pmid=20452111}}</ref>、治療、管理和使用。

痛苦與人類的[[意識|意識]]有關，而且經常伴隨著過去的經驗。

造成痛苦的常見示例有：

*     [[需求_(心理學)|需求]]和期望未滿足
*     失去摯愛
*     與社會[[群體|群體]]分離
*     來自外部的約束和限制
*     [[老化|老化]]、[[疾病|疾病]]和[[疼痛|疼痛]]等<ref>vgl. [[Brockhaus_Enzyklopädie,_21._Auflage|Brockhaus Enzyklopädie, 21. Auflage]]: „Leid, Sammelbegriff für alles, was den Menschen körperlich und seelisch belastet, …“ [[Meyers_Konversations-Lexikon|Meyers Enzyklopädisches Lexikon]], 9. Auflage: „Leid, Schmerz, Krankheit, … v.a. seel. Betrübnis. Die Frage nach Ursprung, Zweck und Überwindung des L.s ist in der Religionsgeschichte sehr unterschiedl. beantwortet worden. …“ Das Große Dudenlexikon (o. J.): „Leid, menschl. Grunderfahrung der Unterbrechung des glückl.-friedvollen Lebensverlaufs, …“</ref>

痛苦是人類的基本體驗。感受痛苦的深度是[[主觀|主觀]]的，取決於[[個人|個人]]，即個人的經歷和態度。

==字源==
在漢語中，痛，是指肉體上的[[疼痛|疼痛]]，而苦，則是來自於[[味覺|味覺]]上的[[苦|苦]][[澀|澀]]感覺，將這兩種感覺結合，就形成痛苦這個詞。痛苦是一個概括性的形容語，肉體上產生的疼痛感受，可以稱為痛苦，而心靈上的煩惱掙扎，也可以稱為痛苦。

